public class OrderProcessor {

    private Map<String, Integer> priceList;

    public OrderProcessor(Map<String, Integer> priceList) {
        this.priceList = priceList;
    }

    public int calculateOrderPrice(String orderString) {
        String[] orderData = orderString.split("\\s+");
        String[] productDetails = orderData[0].split("â€“");

        // Query price using the product name
        int productPrice = queryPrice(productDetails[1]);

        int orderPrice = Integer.parseInt(orderData[1]) * productPrice;
        return orderPrice;
    }

    private int queryPrice(String productName) {
        return priceList.get(productName);
    }
}
```

**Explanation:**

* The `calculateOrderPrice()` method takes the order string as input.
* It splits the string into order data and product details.
